4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REQUIRING COVERAGE OF CERTAIN TREATMENTS AND
5 MEDICATIONS RELATING TO DIABETES, OBESITY, OR POLYCYSTIC OVARY SYNDROME; PROVIDING
6 THE TYPES OF TREATMENTS AND MEDICATIONS THAT MUST BE COVERED; PROVIDING WHAT
7 MEDICAL NECESSITY INCLUDES; PROVIDING EXCLUSIONS; APPLYING TO CERTAIN INSURED
8 GROUPS; AND AMENDING SECTIONS 2-18-704, 33-31-111, AND 33-35-306, MCA.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Coverage of certain treatments and medications relating to diabetes
13 and obesity. (1) (a) Each individual disability policy, certificate of insurance, and membership contract that is
14 delivered, issued for delivery, renewed, extended, or modified in this state must provide coverage for:
15 (i) glucagon-like peptide-1 receptor agonists if it is determined to be medically necessary; and
16 (ii) polycystic ovary syndrome if it is determined to be medically necessary.
17 (b) For the purposes of subsection (1)(a), the term "medically necessary" includes but is not limited
18 to a diagnosis of diabetes or class 3 obesity or polycystic ovary syndrome.
19 (2) Coverage under this section may be subject to deductibles, coinsurance, and copayment
20 provisions. Special deductible, coinsurance, copayment, or other limitations that are not generally applicable to
21 other medical services covered under the plan may not be imposed on coverage of glucagon-like peptide-1
22 receptor agonists. A health insurance issuer may use cost containment measures, which may include but are
23 not limited to step therapy and prior authorization.
24 (3) This section does not apply to disability income, hospital indemnity, the Montana medicaid
25 program provided for in 53-6-101, medicare supplement, specified disease, the state employee group benefit
26 plans provided for in Title 2, chapter 18, part 7, or long-term care policies.
